\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Could you give me your full name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Robert Adam Ferguson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 2 Kirklee Gardens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Are you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Never was married. Bachelor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What year were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 18 - 1891.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Where about were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 In Gorrock. Scotland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 That's just a bit towards the other end of the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clyde{\*\xmlclose} isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 It's - leading out to the sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - three months. It was a holiday house you see. We had a house in Glasgow at the same time. The rest were all born in Glasgow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was it just coincidence that you were born in Gorrock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No. We had a house attached the shop you see, down - down for the summer. Just two months - two - two months in the summertime and I was born there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 So after the three months there you came back to Glasgow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes. And I've been there - there ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Whereabouts in Glasgow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Nathieson Street.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Is that to the east?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 South.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How long did you live there for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh long - good number of years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When did you move?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 The most were either - were born in Mathieson Street. We moved - to, I think it was - Waddel Street, just round the corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What years was that, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well roughly that would be - 1900 I would say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you move again after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh we moved a lot of times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When was the next move, how old would you be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Fourteen. Started work at fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you move with the family then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Where did you go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 To - Caledonia Road I think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Same district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 All the same district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you move again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh moved quite a lot of times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you remember why the family moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well - it was - accommodation - bigger accommodation. See - we were all growing up you see. And you had - you got a house}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 old of boys you see it wasn't too bad. One girl.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh my father would - my father died when he was forty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What year did he die?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 1900.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 So he was born in 1860?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 1891 and he was born in 1860.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 So he'd be thirty-one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye, he'd be that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 He came from Slamaman, in - Lanarkshire I think it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 He was a publican wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did he have another job before he became a publican?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh yes, he worked for the railway before he was - got a license.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What did he do on the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 He - I think he was a guard. Positive guard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Had he any job after he became a publican?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, he - that was his - he died when he was in the - pub - public }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 license
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did he ever do any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was he ever out of work that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Not - not - not that I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I'd say about thirty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Glasgow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Had she any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 She - she worked at a mill. The mils in these days. I think it - made - flags and that. Colour printers. It was all women labour in 
the mills, mostly all women. But they're defunct now. It was a Fergus Mill. Made flags, Union Jacks and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did she work after she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Not even part time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 After your father died did she go back to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. We were too young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did she in fact work until she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 She - she never worked at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How many rooms were there in the house that you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 One room. One room and a kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What were the rooms used for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Be - two beds in one room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 And the kitchen for eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 And living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was there a bed in the kitchen too?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Sometimes there was wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes. Oh yes. That's what they call - an apron
. Fenced off - fenced off from the kitchen with a curtain. Curtain - kept the - kept the view away from it. But they could be sleeping there when you - and everything was going on. Aye. Name for the What is it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was it something like truckle bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Concealed bed. - Mor a concealed bed they called it. Mean it was hidden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did anyone else besides your parents and your brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Nolodgers or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Too many of us. Need all place for ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was the washing done at home or was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Done at home. 'Course they had wash houses in these days. And you could take it round the corner where - a Corporation would
 be. In Rowden Road I think - just about five or ten minutes from the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What was in these wash houses, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh I never saw it. No. Carried the - stuff round to the wash house but that was only just the side of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Your mother used to do it herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your mother or your father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 They were bought were they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 All bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were they bought new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Mostly all new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you remember where they were bought from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh well - didn't take no notice. Shop in Rattan Road, Kings they called it. It's a bairn - all childrens outfitters - shop. Trousers. I remember I had them, they used to have short trousers, got a button at the k
new, they called them knickerbockers. The stockings - fastened inside the trousers, in the buckle - in the button. They have them - more like a golfers outfit. Or - or - or a plus four, gentleman sort of style.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you remember how often the clothes were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Well it was near about at the one time because - if you go once - somebody else's turn came next. Of course we were well off for - as far as that was concerned because the - the shop was sold. See there was none of us old enough to get in
to that trade at all. The - the eldest was fifteen - thirteen or fifteen. Fifteen. So they don't give you a licence }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 for public}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
 house - public house and then my mother wouldna take - nothing to do with the public house. She didna like it. Mother was inside the shops. She - did - didna like the trade at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 That was when your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about shoes, did your father ever make or mend your shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Going - I had to go to the cobblers. In these days it was awful handy, th
ere was always wee shops round the corner. Didna need to go far for a cobbler in those days. They were one man businesses usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I believe they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 centers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784  for meetings and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I don't - I can't answer that. No meeting places, I
'll tell you they hard work - worked long hours. If a man was busy he stayed on at night and - did - if you said you wanted them for the night you got 'em. The - the overtime with these things you know 'cos he - he - he was-the partner. Some of them had t
h
eir sons in them of course. 'Cos I mind they used to put the tacks - in their mouth and - you'd be - poisoned if you did that nowadays, but these men did that between their teeth, kept a nail in between their teeth, to save - for picking one at time, put 
two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 in, one in their mouth.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were your shoes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
All new. You couldna get secondhand these days, they were nearly - all of the - well the shoes were - these sand shoes you wore in the summertime, they were one and sixpence ha'penny a pair. These white ones that you're seeing about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 now. We used to get a pair of them for the three months holidays off of school. Leave your - good shoes - off for a while. Or - Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What sort of shoes would you wear in the winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Leather shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you ever wear clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How often would your shoes be bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh - do you for a year. Repaired maybe twice. Sometimes it was just heels you know Heels that you - put them on when you got them next day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
I wouldna say he was a handyman about the house. He was - he was - engrossed in his own - business, these days it was long hours. The show opened at - public houses opened eight o'clock in the m
orning. And they was open 'til eleven at night. Fifty years - they don't do bad now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 So he never had much time for things like cleaning or cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Never done that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. 'Cos me mother was a fit woman, very fit woman you see. Never had an illness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about decorating and repairs and things like that, did your father ever do any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I've seen him doing a bit of that. Painting or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about helping to look after the children, did he dress or undress you, bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Nothing like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did he ever read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did he ever look after you while your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No. See mother always - a crowd of us you see. We didna need - went - where one went two - two or three went, would be you see - with the football ground, it was only seven minutes from the house. We used to get - ball and away over the green. Come back
 late. A tub - a big - sink bath and that - cleaned up and put to bed, or we put ourselves to bed. Of course we were lucky that way, we had good health. A good - we never had a doctor in the house at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you have any jobs that you had to do at home regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. 'Cept - brushing our shoes and - doing these things you know, you wash your face and hands - before you get your bed by yourself.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 But you didn't have jobs like scrubbing floors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. None of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about your sister, did she have any jobs to do round the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No, she was a bit of a lady, my mother being so healthy - she let her go - to her work, and as long as she attended to her work - that was all she wanted. 'Course - the family and that were all growing
 up you see, there was always some - as soon as you start work, it's no long 'til the next one goes to work. Two years difference you see. And that's how you see the difference with the year. My sister's a lot of good jobs, she's a clever girl. She could 
do - knit things and - socks. She's very handy with a machine. Made a lot of money just for her - own use practically, well I mean - to get things for herself. Which was - nobody - challenge that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your older brothers help you with things that you found difficult when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, we all fend for ourself like. We fought one another - watched one another - to take the grade from the top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did the older children ever help you with things like dressing or eating?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Or look after you in anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I canna mind, things like that, they were all able to eat for themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Not even when you were very little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Five years of age I think or six years. See we used to be - the school was next to the - building and we j
ust dived in it after - after come out of school and got a piece of jelly or whatever it was and away out again. Of course that was the - benefit of that recreation ground being there, you know, all the boys went away to this park. To play football.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did the younger children help the older in any way, did you you're your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I can't mind a doing this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your sister ever help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well so I could - when I looked - if they did well for themselves - that was my; mother's motto,
 if you do well for yourself you do well for me sort of style. She brought them all up that way. As long as we worked - she'll do - she would - house were all days. She loved - she never happier than when she's at home. If she went out visiting she'd say,
 ach - I'd rather be at home and doing something here than with somebody else sort of style. Of course other folks were like mother that way. There wasn't the same visiting done in these days - entertaining or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh aye, before ten. Up to ten p.m. when you got a wee bit - you were always in before ten. I was never - I was never out after ten when I was a young man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 O
h - well we played to about seven o'clock, it got dark anyway. Home, packed - packed in a game at that time you know and was ready for lying down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you were small did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, we think we managed to do t
hat ourselves. We'd got our clothes and you - put them on yourself. You were brought up that way. The one didn't help the other, you'd - unless - something stuck you know. That wasna very often 'cos they - they pick up quick with watching one another. Put
ting on socks and things like that. Stockings and - pants. It's the first thing you learn really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What age do you think you were when you started to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh I'd say about seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would your mother do it before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I think so, if you were tired she just - put you to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you share the bedroom or the bed with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh yes, I shared the bed. Two brothers at one time. Were good beds - big beds. Plenty of room. Few squabbles you know and that. But I'll tel
l you a funnier thing yet. I - I've been sleeping myself solo for fifty - over fifty years. Not a person in that bed. Wherever I've been, I've always - always been single. And I'm a single man. I feel - when my brother used to visit me after he married li
k
e - and I was the only one that - I stayed with my mother until she died, well if they came to visit us, they got a bed to theirself. 'Course the - bigger - bigger houses then. But when we were only our two selves we kept a - a big spare bed for anybody c
oming. So as I wouldna - have to sleep with any of the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I don't suppose you could could you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
It - it's very difficult. I - I've never known to - to do it yet you see. And even now I mean the same thing happened, every man in his own bed, well - that didn't affect me that, because I was well used to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you were small you and two brothers would sleep in one bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about the rest of the family, would you all be sleeping in the one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Mum and dad as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 They'd be in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 That's right. Kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - it was in the kitchen the bath. Front of the fire.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 A big tub bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 A zinc - zinc bath. Two handles, one each end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Friday night was your bathnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Same night. Saturday - you were dressed Saturday - Sunday sort of dress, Sunday and Saturday - Saturday and Sunday, so you get the diffe
rent for your school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 wear you see. When you're at school you just had the jersey and the pants and the shoes and - you we}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 ar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784  coat whatever it was, or your jacket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 The kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were there any occasions that you remember from your childhood when you ate in - another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, canna mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did she have a range or a gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 It was a - a range with coal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh eight o'clock in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who was there, the whole family or just the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh no, they're all - start at different hours you see. It all depended who - who was going out first. They - none of them had the same time. Of course I had the
 same times all my life. I never started before nine o'clock in my life. Nine o'clock in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would your father eat breakfast with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh no, he was away - before that. The shop was open at eight o'clock. So that cleared the road for th
at. And then the next two would be away, they would come in and - it was like in rotation 'til you got them finished.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When would your mum have her breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - anytime, after she got - rid of us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What did you usually eat for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh porridge and - every morning. Butter and - jam and tea, that was about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you have anything different on certain days, a Sunday for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 We had soup - soup. Made at home, homemade soup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was that for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What else would you have for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Sausage and potatoes or something. Veg and potatoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What would you have to eat in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - bit cheese or - cheese was very cheap in these days. Sixpence a pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about your father, would he have the same meals as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh he had - he took his meals to the sometimes. In the main he did, because it's open - it had to be kept open all the time, you don't - canna shut proper hours in these days, for dinner and tea. Had to be open - open all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did she bottle any fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about making pickles?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about beer being brewed for your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No beer used.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about wine, did she make any wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about medicines, did she ever concoct her own medicine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh no, it was - it was Gregory's mixture. We got the same thing all the 
time. Horrible tasting, I don't mind - I never took much of that. Never take medicine in my life much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables or fruit at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, no place to grow fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did they buy them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes, they had to buy all these things. Potatoes. Peas. And - fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did they have tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I don't mind her getting these at all. It's long before the tinned fruits I'm afraid. The war made that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your family keep any livestock like hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How many times a week would you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh well - wouldna get it every day. Every second day it would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
ever get any extra meat from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you ever remember seeing your mother have less food so the family could have more?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
There was - we - oh she would ask you if you wanted anymore of a certain things. Some didna take much and others took - different they - some - one broth
er could eat a whole lot very near, he - he was a - eater you see because he was - his work. But for me, I never was a big eater in all - all the days of my life. If I take porridge that - fills me up too much for - couldna take the good things that was c
oming after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about meals on Sundays, did you get anything different on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Have soup and potatoes. Soup and potatoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you have a roast on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, it was - much the same as for school week. There wasna much - g
reat variation you know - the menu all the time and - it suited them, they got used to it, there was less squabbling about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you think that your mother ever had a smaller helping so that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 you children could have more food when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No, I never heard her complain, no. Because - she used to tell us, I had a week cup of tea - of tea when you're all - cup of tea on my own. Peaceful cup of tea. That's when it come to eleven o'clock he would sit down, say - thank God for that, I've got 
a rest now. But she wanted you know, to see them growing up. And when - no having the - the doctor coming in. Oh she was a wonderful mother. She was a homebird all the time. She'd go away on holiday for a week, she would say, I'm glad to come back to my a
in place. Be it ever so humble, there's no place like home she said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you ever remember seeing your father have more food than the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 It was only at the weekend I saw him with his food because of the - he didna come in for his food yo
u see, he got it at the shop. And he had - had utensils for doing it himself there whatever he wanted you know, he just - got a couple of pies and boil them and - two or three - two or three slices of bread or something like that. Simple but - nutritious.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I never talked much at meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you allowed to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh yes. You see you get some who say, I don't like this. Well, if you don't like it you just lump it, she used to say. So you took it and say nothing - you never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784  you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 never complained much about it, you know you hadna got to get any extra.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh just took - you got your portion. 
Was cut - portions for you, save any - putting a plate - a separate place for yourself. But the bread was just put in the centre, a big - you could pick as much bread as you wanted of course but - it averaged a slice and a slice and a half of bread, nobod
y take any more than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well they didn't appreciate it, give you a row for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 If there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask for it or did you have to wait for it to be passed to you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
You'd ask for it, pass it to you. Pass it round. But in these things you see, although there were seven - eight of us - very seldom you'd get - at the - the table at the one time. The only chance
 is at the weekend. They've all got different hours I'm telling you, and - when the work - they - they'd all come in at the same time, one after the other maybe. That - keeps it going to about six at night, and seven at night sometimes before the - the wh
ole lot's cleared away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye, I think you could but I doubt if I ever did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would you have got one do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh I dare - daresay I would get something but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you have a knife and fork or was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784  it a spoon, quite often sp}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 ns were used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 There wasna so much knife and fork business in these days at all. Things that you would - would - would look - look funny nowadays.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 did you used a spoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Sp}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
on - well a spoon for some things. Spoon for your soup. Spoon for your tea - tea - what they call a teaspoon. Soup spoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you expected to sit in a certain way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Could you bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Get them flung on the floor I doubt. Put away - plenty of time for these books after that. Must get this cleared up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 We used to have to say, can I leave the table and get out to - see somebody to play? Away you go then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did all the family sit at the table for a meal, all the family where were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 From them that's in maybe, make one - one scoop from that all that's in, get it over with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. First one that was empty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How was the meal served, who served it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would she put it on the plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes. Have to - try to divide it equally you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - no - no special order.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Where would your younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 It's very difficult to think - to say that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you ever remember there being a high chair or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 They would perhaps be just on your mother's knee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who would feed them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - mother would feed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What age did they join in family meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - about six. When they go to school. You just came in from school and sit - draw a chair and sit there at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Very easy. Even tempered. Never seen that woman - was not ill in her life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was she affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 If you'd had any worries could you share them with her when you were a little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No, I was one of the kind that kept them all to myself. If I'd a - quarrel wi' a boy outside and we had a wee bit - tussle, I never told her about it. Just - went and - washed my hands and face. Sat down as if nothing had ha
ppened. She used to sit there - I don't know how a woman can stand that. Having so many children. And yet they expected them to stay that way. It's better than having tow or one. Aye. You see because you - you're attention's taken away from your mother. I
f you see your brother going one place you - apt to follow suit. And that's it - it's only the watching the - how - how they do a thing that you became - good at it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 If you had wanted to share whatever worries you had with your mum would you have felt that you could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No. I wouldna ha' told her. No. Because I knew she'd enough on her plate. And - I didn't tell her you see, some people would do that, but I'm one of these people, keep - keep things to myself. Being so much alone. You don't - think of
 telling anybody anything at all in fact. And yet I could write a book - about putting yourself there, my experiences. You know, being a bachelor, you - you - you don't have the - hear - havena got the same troubles as what married people have to go throu
g
h them. Every days the same to you - to the - a bachelor. And I really - I used to think it was terrible for a woman to get left with six in a family and - bring them up. I used to think to myself, I wouldna like to do that. I'd rather - do without. And y
e
t it's - peculiar, a gamble a lottery you know. Life is a lottery you know. It's a big gamble. Some people are successful - without any effort. And others - all life was - never bring any successes to them. Well I had a record that I think I was fifty - t
w
o years with one firm. From the day I left school 'tol the day I retired. Now - you take another brother of mine, that fellow couldna stay in a job long. Of course, his was more manual work you see, and I'm the staff you see. And I go about with my bowler
 
hat on - from morning 'til - stopping time. My pay was on - very regular. Never got a penny off my pay in fifty-two years. Holidays were paid for too, when a lot of people - didn't get paid for their holidays - staff - the office got their pay. But the wo
rkers weren't. It's more unified now that of course. It was bound to come. And I used to think it funny myself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Your father died when you were nine didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 He died in 1900. Well I would be nine then, I was 1891, nine then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh - very good fellow. Very domineering. See, hew as - opposite from my mother. See, he - he didna take much to do with the family at all. Him being - engrossed, as she said, in his business. This is what I know, she kept him a lo
t of things that didna happen sometimes. Such as - so and so's sick or - he's gone to his bed, he's got a cold. She never told him. To save him. I'd say he - in these days a one man business was a hard thing you know. Some men have a one man business but 
they've got a family - to help them, but at that age you couldn't do nothing for him. In fact wouldn't be allowed inside the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was your father an affectionate person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I wouldn't say he was. He was - he was out to - make for himself and - 
but - he died of a heart attack you see. He never had any illnesses you see. Just - that were his first illness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 He died suddenly did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 He left his shop at - shut his shop about eight o'clock and he's dead two hours after. Strained heart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh well they expected - my mother expected - said as long as the - I attended to my work - look after myself, that was her main - major worry. She said, if you all do that it'll save me a lot o
' - worry. But then - we come to the 1914 war. And the house never was the same after that. The war broke that all up. One brother got married. During his time in the - Army. He was in Aberdeen with the Gordon Highlanders and he got married the year war s
t
opped, 1918. After that another one, John, he got married and then - the sister got married. And the house became empty again - our house. Of course when my mother and I were left alone we were quite happy about it and we - we had no worries at all. Was n
ever a doctor inside the door. And then we knew one another's times, we were as regular as the clock. If I was going to be late I'd - let her know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents bring you - up to behave towards your brothers and sister in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Now 
I wouldna say that because - the - the although we had five brothers, they - they didn't do a lot together you know. As they grew up - when they start to work, they make - they make their workmates and that - that's their playmates after that. You get 'em
 going into a - a town for instance. I was fourteen years of age before I bothered to go into town at all. Although I was in it for fifty-two years and never out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents say you should hit back or not if another child hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No,
 I don't think they applied that at all really. But - wee scuffles like that - they know - they knew, the school was just next - and they could see what was happening. Two boys fighting after four o'clock - when the school come out, had a grudge, a wee gr
u
dge. And they used to - faced up to one another but they couldna burst a paper bag you know but - but it's - it was funny to see that. Nothing like that in the school nowadays, I think they're bet - better - disciplined, even now than what they were then.
 For they had the janitor and that for to keep you in order. You mustn't play football in the street, always in the school, various - paltry things. It was - that was mainly his job, it was more of a policeman's job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped that you and your brothers and sister would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh well they expected you to do right and - attend to your work and your home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh well, they taught you you must behave yourself and keep out of trouble and all that sort of thing, don't - get into trouble and that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well - swearing wasna so common these days as what it is now. Nor the same vandalis
m when you're young like that, it's a - a different thing altogether, it's paltry things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you ever hear your parents swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I can - very rarely. I never heard my mother swear in her life. But the old man, yes, he said it a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you were little when the grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 If you did something your parents disapproved of what would happen to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well you'd get clout on the ears.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who'd give you a clout?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Your fath
er. My mother wouldn't. Of the two of them he - he'd - he did all the clouting. The Sunday morning, with you waking up that was - the - the time he - you had made too much noise, he couldn't bear to hear any, and that was - and it stop - turned the noise 
t
o a - silence. 'Course they lifted their hand but they didna - mean to be brutal you know. And then - they didna spoil you with money the way they do nowadays. For all my father had a shop he wasna that he - he didna spoil you. But at the weekend he gave 
y
ou - he you gave you a few coppers each you know. Got your pay. Pocket money. In these days threepence was a lot of money you know. And of course - I didna smoke 'til I was fourteen, 'til I started work. Now I smoke - I've been smoking twenty cigarettes a
 day all my life. Six and tuppence they cost. Every time, twenty of that, six and tuppence. It's about two pound a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh aye, I got a few turns like the rest of them I think. Can'
t remember yet. Coming in wi' your - boots all - dirt. Just coming into the kitchen and then - get these off. Get these off. Sit down and get the clay off them. You didna get - a moment 'til it was done to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Because that was your one and only pair of shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you remember how - you felt about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No, I think you get used to it, if you get it often you don't think the same about it. But - if you get it a - a spell away fro' it, it takes more effect. You'll no get t
wo in a family the same - same nature you know. Five brothers and there's - there's they're as different as day and night sometimes you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or from one more than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No, I took it from my mother, I thought her way was the easiest way. The quarrelling way - is no use. So as you grow older you keep away from all these - squabbles if you can avoid them. Sometimes you canna avoid it of course but - y
ou don't need to be in it if you can keep away from it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh yes, you'd get a dumpling. Fruity dumpling. And you heard about it a week before it come you know. You had dumpling for
 a few nights after it too. Toasted dumplings. They put it in the oven after - they finished dishing it out, what was - steam used to come off the cloth you know and - like roll. You each got your - portion. It's a - it's a great thing yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you used to get presents on your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh yes, it depended - what age you were you know. But the tie business was the great thing you know, aye. Tie or a - gloves or - pair - a pair of - not dear gloves, these woolen gloves, they used to be about - shilling a pair something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would you have a party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I wouldna say that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Any children from school come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Nothing like that, I mean, there'd be - enough of ourselves for to - have a party you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No, there werena - great frivolities these days, it was - you were at home, you know, wee bit extra - Christmas dinner, wee bit extra. That was about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about New Year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No, we used to go to the Sunday school. They give you a party at the New Year. And the boys - sometime they - a Friendly Boys Religious Society, they went Christmas like. You got an orange and - and a paste - cup - couple of pastries and a cup of tea.
 Yes, that was - every year that happened and - they've all died out, these things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you have any musical instruments in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well - one brother learned the fiddle. But he never made anything out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was there a piano there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 The sister played the piano. That's her that's in Chester, she's - she'll be about sixty-nine now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye, the sister sang a wee bit too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, wou
ldna say we did much, it was when strangers was in it was all - it was used most you know, somebody coming up to see them. Bring up like - friend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, not a 
great deal. Well books were - I used to get prizes from the school. And so did the other brothers, and these things collected you know. For perfect attendance you got - what was it - aye, you got a book. You got perfect attendance you all got a prize.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about newspapers and magazines, did you get those at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye, we used to get all the - well, the Sunday papers, newspapers and the evening paper. You had the Citizen. And - the Times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh yes. Well not so much books but - peoples journals and all that sort, my mother read all her own kind of books. Father, he was - just the evening paper and - and advertisements and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you remember attending a funeral in your family when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, wasna - wasna any funerals save as we were growing up. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you remember a funeral at all in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 One that you actually didn't go to but one that happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes, that's what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
We were ever - ever so young we were. I don't - say they all weren't allowed to go but there were two that - two that - the two eldest went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who attended the funeral, was it the menfolk or the men and women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, no women at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your mother go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you wear mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Black tie, that was about all. As long as you had a black tie and a dark coat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your mother wear mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784  they used to buy mourning cloth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 es after the - they went in mourning for a short time. Aye, but - it's not so common nowadays is it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How long would your mother have stayed in mourning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - six month, 'til the - frock was finished sort of style. Sunday - going out on a Sunday and that. Not through the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you remember if you had the coffin overnight in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How was it taken to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 From - oh well, the hearse comes to the door and - put into the hearse. And the coaches are just at the back of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was it a horsedrawn hearse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 With black horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Whit horses. No, black horses. Or brown, dark brown. Not white horses but - that was for - marriages that they had 
them. Used to go white horses for marriages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did the mourners walk behind the coffin or did they go in a coach?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Depending the distance. See, cannae - th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 ere were elderly people couldnae}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784  walk the distance. So you usually have carriage - two coach
es - coming at the back, with eight people, they could hold about six - twelve people. That was - an average - size of a funeral then, about a dozen. Now the women don't go to them here yet even I don't think. Of course the weather's all against that too 
but - too dangerous in winter, for grief stricken they get - drenching, that's the finish of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you were little were you taken out visiting neighbou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 s, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who would take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would she take all of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, no. Just the - the younger ones, the youngest ones, the ones that couldna look after theirself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Occasionally I went out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Where would he take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh - for a walk, to some of the parks. Or run in - run in the car, it was horse cars then. They didna go far out you know, they just went out to a - certain place, you get - dropped off. End of the line you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you remember any other outings with your parents, such as Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh no, we used to go to our holidays to - Rothesay. Dunoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 That was a proper holiday was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
t's a fair holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 That would be a fortnight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye. But these days it wasn't so much as that, sometimes you only had ten days. It's a fortnight really you would take it as I would say.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would you go away regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, no. You see - my mother used to go away with her sister. When the holidays come on. She would go to
 down to her house, she'd stay there for a couple o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
 days and come back up again. Then when she went away her sister would come down for her and that. Just a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was this when you were old enough to look after yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye, when you were - you were well - make a cup of tea and - feed yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you went away with your mother and father to Rothesay - did your father go away with you before he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you ever go for a holiday with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Very - don't mind it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about days out, did he ever take you for a day out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh aye, he took us - I've seen us - a Sunday he would take us out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Whe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
e would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - Gorrock or - Elsborough, some of these places not too far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 You say you had a holiday house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye, at the time he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you own it or did you rent it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No, it was built - part of the shop - the shop, it's the same - it's like a - the house is up above the - shop. You go in to the one side to go up to the house but - th
e public go in the front door. Aye. But the place is up - the house is up the stairs. But these are what you call - I don't know what you'd call them, Sunday hotels and - see, you had meals and you can drink on a Sunday, you couldna get that - in Glasgow 
that time. They had a special license you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you went away for holidays to Rothesay did the whole fam}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 i}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 ly go, apart from your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, no, some of them would go on their own roads and - they would go a bit - see, the Boys Brigade used t
o have a camp and two of them went to that. And that, but - the other ones that were left would go down - down to - Rothesay for that. Oh, that was a favourite haunt at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Rothesay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 And Dunoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What sort of things would you do when you were on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 We did fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What would your mother do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh she j}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590695\charrsid14161784 ust go down to the front and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 get into the - sightseeing, all - watching all the boats going out and coming in. A big - verandah there for the - people sit there for - couple of hours in the afternoon, the sun shining.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would your sister go with your mum?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you tell me how you spent Saturday in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well I used to go to a football match.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 To watch or to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 To watch. No, to p
lay up 'til I was fourteen and then when I went to work I started pay my shilling or sixpence whatever it was to go in and see it. Probably it was Celtic and Rangers and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about Sundays, how would you spend Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh that was a - a terrible day Sunday. Nothing to do at all. Read and lounge and sleep and knock about that was about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you have to wear different clothes on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - you'd to keep your good - put - your Sunday - Saturday and Sunday suit, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you allowed to play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, you werena supposed to play football on Saturday but - they did it. In the big open spaces - away from the houses altogether.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents think it wrong to play or to work on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I don't think t
hey liked you to play on a Sunday like. 'Course there was simple things you know. More simple. More contented. didn't need to l-ok for too much these days. Nowadays that wouldna suit them at all, they'd go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, my - they did not. But they made sure that we went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What denomination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 We used to go to a morning meeting and the Sunday school. Twice a day on the Sunday you could go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What denomination was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Protestant. Methodist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 You used to go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye. If you - if you didna go to Sunday school you didna get to the Sunday school trip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was the Sunday school trip once a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye. We used to get a tinny. Aye. A - a tin with a handle on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 To drink out of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye. Bring it so as they - they filled it for you as much times as you wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Where would they take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well, Busby. That's up the Clyde somewhere. Muirend. Crookston Castle. Galahouston. Places all within - say three mile
. You wonder how they got teachers for to do that, look after all these kids. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were there any other social activities organised by the church that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well - The Founder Boy's was one I mind. It was a religious society and - ha
d a football club and - called the Founder Boys Society. Glasgow Religious Society. Glasgow Founder Boys Religious Society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was it a temperance club?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Branches all over Glasgow, the - every district had a - hall of their own where they met. 
A gym - gymnastics and all that sort of thing. Different - different nights of the week. Youth clubs, just what you would call a youth club now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did the church run a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. But - you were supposed to be a - a non - drinker if you were - that was the - that was their mainstay - against strong drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you have to sign the pl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 dge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 You had a membership card after you - when you joined. A member ship cared and - that gave you all 
your - instructions. Some may have spent their lifetime at that. One man was fifty years at it I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you have to sign the pledge at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. But - this - kept them off - I think so. A lot of them nae joined it of course but - it was there for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you belong to any other club organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 None at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh I think it would be - would be more - the Conservative way. If you've got your own premises you don't vote Labour, if you're not working manual labour you don't vote that nowadays.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your mother take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you remember your father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I don't know what he voted but he voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 In some places at that time men felt that they risked losing their jobs or their h
ouse if they voted differently from their employers, do you think your father ever felt like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No. I don't think so. Of course I would say that - they would be all Labour in - depends on class of work. But he could earn - a man is - making money 
for himself must vote Conservative. He's not - philanthropist you know, he's - that's how Labour is such a strong thing it is - is today. It's a matter of - the working man against the capitalist. I never was in a union in my life. And that's fifty-two ye
ar at the firm I was with - the workers were all trade unionist. The print - the printing trade are all trade unionists.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 So you don't think your father felt himself under any particular pressure to vote for any party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, he wasn't. So engrossed 
in that - politics wasna so - talked about so much in these days. Advancement in fifty years had been terrific. And the next fifty years there'll be no King and Queen. Less than that. The way things is going. You'll lost that as sure as gun. Because - you
'
ll not get the right men to stand - stand for Parliament. They know they're up against - the peoples up against them, no matter who they are. And yet I thought trade union was - a good thing when I - you know, to keep - the working man - not - not - being
 
drudged down all the time. To give him a fair wage. But now it's reached the stage now - they want money for nothing. And they don't care whether the firm's got the money to pay it or no, they just - say that's O.K. Whereas when I was - trades union was o
nly in it's - getting on its pins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 That's when you first started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh aye. But you had - the firm I was with, it was a trades union shop, you couldna get a job by - if you were a tradesman you had - you have a trades union card.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 That was the printing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was your father}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 or mother ever members of a political party?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. I don't think so. Too much - too - too many other things to think about than politics there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When your parents weren't working how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh my mother had - knitted all her own socks, for five boys and she was at it all the time. Knitting and sewing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What sort of things did she sew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well she'd sew - jumpers anything like that, what they have now, jerseys. Call 
them jerseys these days. She bought the wool, it was navy blue, I used to get a navy blue one. Another one would get a brown one or something like that. But it was different, wool was cheap. You could get a lot of wool for two shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about your father before he died, when he wasn't working what would he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh he never had time for anything. The business was - he was tired when he got home at night, he never had much time to - be on the go all day and - when he got home at night he was ready for lying down. The hours were too much for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No, none at all. Too much - of her own too do. She - she would have liked to have done but she didna - tickle it because she couldna keep it up. But she was a - law abiding and - and very religious woman. She believed in the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I've seen her going to - a music hall when it was - the Palace, maybe go out on a - Friday night, one night a week. Or go to the}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
flickies, what it was then. It was - cinematograph shows. The one round the corner, it was only a few coppers then you see. If a next door neighbour used to - say, come on, we'll get a - change for a wee while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 She'd go out with her next door neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What time did your father get home from work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Eleven o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh no, no Sunday. No Sunday work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What would he do on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh, he'd read, sleep.
 Have a nap in the afternoon. Go out at night for a walk. Back in again. Now in that line he hadn't the same chance of making up with company for - you'd no time to - you canna spare the time to go with you - with - with any Tom, Dick and Harry. There wer
e
 no cars in these day what you could do a run in an hour and get away. Oh I'm living handsomely now compared with what I did. See but it - they're not as happy. People were contented in these days. You never heard a man - saying he'd chucked his job or an
ything like that. These were things you never heard of - they were so engrossed in - thought themselves lucky that they were working. See, you no want money for - big - big money, they don't want to work for nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your father attend any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Oh he was a - he was a Mason, he was a Free}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 ason. I was a Freemason too. Only one in the family. I'm the odd man out in everything. Single. 'Course I could go anywhere, if you're single you can go anyway, you do't need to ask anybody, can I go, ca
n I do this, and that? You - you can - if anybody asks you to do a thing you're able to say straight way, that'll suit me all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How often did your father attend the Masons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well he belonged to one in Gorrock so I don't know much about it, I
 was too young then. But I was - joined in 1925, I've been to it - fifty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your mother used to go to ladies nights?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I don't know that they had such a thing in these days. These are all advancements now. They have theatre nights now, whe
re their wives and families go - once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your mother ever go down to the pub with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Not at all. She never served a customer in her life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did she ever go for a drink herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Never, she never took drink in her life. She never tasted - whisky in her life. Without - unless it was a doctor's order.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you ever go into the pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Me? Yes, I went in the pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you ever go into your father's?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I was too young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you remember about the pub that he ran, did he used to tell you about it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I - I've thought since then, of a sort. But at that time I couldnae have told you. You see as I say I was only - born then, that's all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 He came to a pub in Glasgow did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 He'd a pub in Glasgow too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who used to look after the pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Well he had to have a man for one shop you see. And he looked after the other himself. See the Gorrock' shop's not much of a shop and - in the wintertime, but in the summer trade it's quite good. It'
s a summer season sort of job. The street is - facing the sea. The shop looks right onto the sea. A lovely view. So she told me I was put out there in the barn be little to - no traffic. And kept there for three hours of the - afternoon when the sun came 
out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 You never actually went into the pubs that your father ran?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did he ever tell you about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, he was very - different that way. He was lucky that his sons all went - didna believe in the pubs. There were none of that way tu
rned out - well you could say they could pass them, but they never made a habit of making it out of place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your father take a drink himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Very - if he had company, that's when - the damage came. Travelers coming in and - paying their acco
unt - he paid his account I should say. And then have a refreshment. Back and forward. So you've got to keep your head on. In them days time for drink didna come into it. Of course - they don't - they wouldn't have been allowed to serve in any of them. To
 - first serve drink at the back of the counter here. You'd be told to - police could have been in any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would he ever come back at night the worse for drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Well I wouldn't know, I never seen him but - it wasna drink that was the cause 
of him at all. For he was a man, I'm saying - for all whisky was very cheap in that days - these days - but - people couldna afford anymore than what they're getting now. And now it's getting - too dear for the working man shortly.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did he ever attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did he ever bet that you know of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Not for funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Or sick clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Nor credit, they didna get any credit. They didna take anything credit. It must be paid and - take it away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 They didn't even save for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well we werena very clannish
. We all went our own roads, as - the older we got - we went our roads, that's what happened. You see, the - the different views of life, the one wants to go to football matches. The other one, he didna care whether he went to a football match or not. And
 if they did go to football matches, it's like their own road, they went to - different games. Say Celtic one - some - some'd gone to see Celtic, others went to see the Rangers. All went their own - didna follow suit you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was that still the case when you were all still young and at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh no, closer at the school of course. You see they hands the same - same get away. You had to stay in our own district as it were.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was there anyone of your brothers or sister that you felt particularly close to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No, I think of them all alike. But never got - engrossed with them you see. Such as - when I joined the Masons - no other brother followed me you know. And yet - my father was one. Of course - in these things like that - you - you must a
dmit the hours to suit. A man that's doing a dirty days job cannae come home and rush out in a collar and tie all done up. Although I say it myself I was very conceited - with dress, I had to be. I had to shave every morning of life, before I went to work
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you were a child at school who did you used to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well all the boys in the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about when you were at home, when you got home from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well you had - a different crowd of - playmates at night - from what you had through the days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were they your brothers and sisters or your neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh neighbours mostly. Well - one - or two of our family went - went with one other crowd and I went in another crowd. Formed wee groups as it were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Whereabouts would you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Well you had to wait 'til the - the - as I tell you we played in Glasgow Green, which is open - a space miles long and it had - goalposts and make up your own - carry your own ball with you. Oh there used to be a lot of us playing ther
e. It used to have all Millgate out practically at that time. They dunna like you stand at the corner in wee groups. Wait until you get tired and then away into the house. Simplest life you could possibly get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you ever play in other peoples houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What games did you play, apart from football, did you play any other games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. I used to go to the music halls, that's what I used to do. When they were chea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784  You could get in for sixpence and fourpence. There was a place in Main St
reet, Princess's Theatre where we used to get in for sixpence. Another one we'd get in for fourpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you were quite small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about theatres and concerts?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well the concerts were very common in these days. Oh you could get in - in any district there's always something like that. Local things.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you used to go to cinemas at all when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well there were no cinemas near but - Punch and Judy shows and had - cinematograph. But not like what you've got now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you went out to play were you allowed to get dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh no, you were supposed to - keep yourself - away without - come in the way you come out. As I say, if you're playing football that's different. You can't really do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would you get a row for getting dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you free to play with anyone you wanted to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents ever discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, didna pick your company at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 You belonged to this one boys club with the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you belong to any other youth club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 While you were at school did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I was wanting to be a printer at first. And when I went into the - thi
s place - they said there were an opening for an office boy and that put me off - I could have got to the printing trades - after that - with the same firm but - I rose sort of swift and they kept me in the office all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you keep any pets when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you collect anything like stamps?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about gardening, did you have a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I have done but not to a great state.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about going for walks when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I used to like to go out for a good walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who would you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh just a chum. If you knew him well enough. Go anywhere wi' him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about bicycling, did you ever do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well we used to - what they call 
three'ha'pence hire bicycle out here, threeha'pence and hour and we used to go - take them out for an hour. And you'd to b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
ing them back by the hour, if you didn't - few more to pay. Push bike you know I'm talking about. Not the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who would you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh your pals, nearest pals you'd got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you take part in any other sport apart from football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. I liked boxing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I did a wee bit. But my job didna suit it you see. If you get marked - it looks terrible the
 next day. 'Course it was only amateurs you know. That's right, it was a youth's boxing club in fact. You know, for young fellows up to sixteen and seventeen. But they usually give up, it's just a sort of craze for a while. They know they cannae - make an
ything out of it you know but it's a pastime. It's all right as a pastime. Once a week we used to go down, every Friday I think - it was. Eight to ten at night, two of us. Watch two or three different - fellows. Punching one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How old were you when you used to do this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh seventeen or sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Your parents used to give you pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your mother continue to give you pocket money after your father had died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I think she did, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 About how much would you get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - a few coppers. Threepence or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would you get it regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye, sometimes we didna get it. But - we managed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What would you spend the money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 More sweeties. Just at the sweety shop. The nearest sweety shop used to get}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 the lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Nobody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Not relations or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Not relations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 If your mother was confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I don't know how she - managed to tell you the truth but - I couldnae have been very often 'cos I don't mind it I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about when she was having your younger brothers or your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I don't mind about these other two. Cannae mind that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh yes, my mother had sisters. She had - one in Dennistown. She'd one on the south side. Two in the South Side. And she had a brother in South Side. Oh she had plenty of - relations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How much did she see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Well very - very little. See this - she did latterly, you know, when she got on in years but not when she was younger. So did they they couldna - they didna visit when they were - when they were past all the family business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your father have relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No he hadn't. Because they were all in Edinburgh and - Roxburgh. Preston Pans. All round Edinburgh district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did he see much of his relatives at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh he was very fon
d of - he visited them. That was where he spent most of his time, he was off. He'd have a day out away down to there, he just went himself. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, not coming into the house. Not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Your parents didn't have many relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, aye, no, not - not in Glasgow. Other way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How much did they see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh once in a year. A yearly visit maybe or something lie that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would they go and stay with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Come back - they went away and come back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Neighbours and that? No, it was all relations that they went to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Nobody local?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
