\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 She had sisters but - they're all 
- they were all - up in years. I'm talking about - ten year ago I think. They've all died within about the last ten years. That's the last of that - generation you could say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did she have any chums that lived nearby, perhaps a neighbour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about your father, did he used to have friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, we wouldn't know much, he never got them about the house. All arranged through business mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Where would he see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh in the town, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 So were any of your parents friends ever invited into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I don't know - I couldna - I couldna remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did neighbours ever call in without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Very - very opposite. Just - pass the time of - good day and - good morning and that sort 
of thing. They never carried on a - more conversations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were they not very friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, they were all for their own - all for their own door sort of style.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10438668\charrsid14161784 neihbours}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. They never went out together at all practically. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements, what do you think your parents did to make their own amusements?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh well, it was outside they needed go for that. Unless they went to the flick or something. Music hall or that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you ever remember them having a game of cards with anybody who came round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Don't think I saw a card in our house in my life. No card players. Outside they did. I've played it outside. Whist. W
hen they started whist drives, they used to have whist drives. I've been a time to these things. You - you get a card for one and six or something. Friday night or - some in winter you see. Football clubs. Whist drives for the - spectators of those.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was this after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 when you were a young man, did you think of some people belonging to one class and some people to another class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye, I would think so. Middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you tell me what the different ones were that you thought of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well - they may be the higher - status you know - and than ordinary working man. May stay out - in a posh house. On the outskirts. Whe
reas the other one had to keep to - local all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Which class would you say that you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh I'd say good working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well, tradesmen who worked for
 a weekly wage. Not the labouring class. Class just a wee bit - above that level - who had to serve their time before they become proficient.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What sort of people belonged to the labouring class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well, the - the - the not so highly educated, they
 cannae get the other job you see. They'dve no chance for office work or anything lie that. So they had to take - the labouring class most of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about people belonging to the higher class, what sort of people would you think they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Wel
l I tell you the - that's what we used to call the middle class. Where the - where they have a - a certain income coming in every week for the work, you've got; that class of people. You've got the man who is not working, he gets nothing. That was your tw
o classes. Of course there were no bureaux in these days. Labour Exchanges.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 If you were out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
You'd to go to the gate and look for it - look for a job. You could do that three times a week it takes some distance from here to Glasgow and these places. Ship}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 yards and that. Most of this district working class here all worked in the shipyards.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 R}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
und here is the very wealthy area isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well, it was all most - most own their own hoses, yes, so you could it - the elite. You won't get much better anywhere than here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh they left that to your own - jurisdiction. You pick your own - friends, you pick your own chums.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you ever told to touch your cap or show respect in some way to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I don't that we were taught but we used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who would you touch your cap to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Lady and a gentleman passing you. Most did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about ministers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Ministers, you were supposed to do the same. Raise your cap. Though you don't know the man sometimes even you did that. Of course you - they were reverent men these days, you don't see that nowadays. Very seldom see a man - doffing his cap to a minister
 nowadays. They're just - as ordinary men now. They seem to be - and God with - had God attached to them when - they were ministers years ago. But now it's a job, they just - a job and any other man expect that job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was there anyone that you called sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Well - when you - well you, not when you're little, you don't - go along with that. Mister it used to bed Yes, mister. Yes missus. Yes teacher. Then when you got older - I don't know what you called them then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you remember anybody calling your parents sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 In the district where you lived, that was Hutcheston wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Hutchestontown. Blackfriars it used to be Hutchestontown, but Blackfriars is done way with now and just call it Hutchestontown.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 In that district who were considered the most important people do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh - business people. If you had a wee shop you'd get - a reverence but - see in these days it was all one man shops mostly. A grocers shop, a butchers shop. A man owned it a
nd served in it himself. The grocer did the same thing. Like a family - more family business. Same with dairies. They were all families. Passed from one to the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you come into contact a lot with business people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Later - later on in life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Not when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Why do you think that they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh it's - background. It's a lot to do with background and - environment. Some schools you see, there's two kinds of schools in these - they had pay
ing schools at that too so they were a - different class altogether, the ones that were paid for. There's a fine school, Hutcheston Grammar School, it was one of the oldest in Glasgow. It was in Hutchestontown. That's where it got its name. Hutche Grammar
 they used to call it, Hutchi for short. Hutchi - instead of saying Hutchestontown they said Hutchi.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What sort of school was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Paying school. So much per year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 People who went there were considered more important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes, in the gramm
ar - some distance to get to some of them. They came from the - the South Side, coming from - you could say - Shorlands maybe and Cathcart. All these outside places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who did the shopkeepers associate with, was your father considered a shopkeeper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Not in the same status as these that - here - talking about, these shops were only open from nine 'til six. Or eight 'til six. They shut at night. Six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - people in the same kind of businesses as theirselves, the like attraction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who did clergymen associate with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh - they - they don't belong to a district you see a clergyman, they belong to outside. May come from Clarkston or - Netherlee. - Cathcart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about teachers, who do you think their friends were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 That's a case we only see them during school hours you see, we never see them after. So after four }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 'clock you say until next morning, nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were there any farmers round about that you knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Farmers? No, nothing - no farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 You were too far into Glasgow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye. No - no farmers - no place at all. You need to go miles out to get that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about employers? Who do you think they associated with, were there any living round you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. They were all - these men - only - you only saw them during the working hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh the middle class again. Yes, in steady jobs and - and - pick their job and that sort of style, they meet with a better cl
ass and of course they go to the - get a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
ked to join the church. And of course that's - these days - if you want a job used to have to get a line from the minister. To - to show your - credentials and that. Even to get a job in the Corporation town bus, in
 these days you had to do that. You wouldn't need to do anything like that nowadays. 'Cos a lot of them nae go to the church now you see. Of course a lot of people say}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 it pays you to join - in these days it paid you - to join the church. You've a better ch
ance of getting success. Not so much of the self made man at all. It's not what you know, it's who you know. That's - that's so - that'll never change all the days of this world. It's now what you know, it's who you - it means if you've friends in busines
s - you've a chance of getting on. But if you're - folks have no money you'll - no hop for you unless you - for the lucky ones, except for the lucky ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What sort of people would you say went to the chapel, were they the same sort of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 We
ll I did - didnae know much about them at all, but - they were very confident going to the chapel. The - the protestants - in these days the Protestants used to go - Have a new suit for to go the church, but the - didna - didna matter so much for them. Th
erefore they got a bigger audience. See if you got a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10438668\charrsid14161784 decent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
 suit for Sunday they don't like to know you when you go to the kirk very near. Or the churches I should say.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you notice any religious troubles at that time between the Catholics and the protestants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Aye, one day a year. What they call - what was it? It's the anniversary of the Battle of the Boyne. When King Willie - King Willie. The Billies and Dans used to fight. With sticks. B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 u}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 t that was only for a day. And the schools used to be near one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I think that still happens doesn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh not so much. It was died - dead - not when I was a - we used to - have a go at them. That was only up to fourteen years of age. After that you forget all over these. Life's to dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say that there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I don't think the - the average working man had nothing to hold. Everything - they - they earned they had
 a way for it to go. Never known these went to the bank the way they do here. No - no savings bank in the house, in a wee tin box they used to keep it. A bank they called it. Tin bank. No, I don't think there were many - working people that - saving bank 
a
ccounts in these days. You could say that the man that's working didna get - got nothing at all. Must have had a terrible time. They couldna go to the next door neighbour for they were nae any better off than their-self, they couldnae - always struggling 
- to get - make ends meet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 In the people that you would have thought of as working class, do you think there were different groups within that large group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well you see, as I get up - as - as - one gets - fixed in better they move away from that 
caliber and try - they move further up the district away to - the next bet sort of - building sort of style. See, your address is an awful lot in these days was - if you stayed out in Glasson you were - you must have money sort of style. Whereas you get i
n the - tenements you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 re just - all the same, working and - same rate of pay for - everyone else, in the same job.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you think that one group of people felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh you'll get - yes, I daresay you can but - they'd show th
at in their dress. It was always - better - fit in their clothes and such things as that. Tidier. You cou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
d see them gradually improving every year as you would think. And another one just sticks - solid. Never worries about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Can you call to mind a family you knew yourself out of one of these groups, perhaps the group that was bettering itself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - get the odd one that - used to - becomes friends with you. School}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 teachers. That's the - one - ones that have - made progress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did any of your friends come from such a family who made progress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
I would say - some of them had - their - one family had a business of their own of course, that's different. And they had it for fifty odd years. Yet the whole family worked. Six or seven of them.
 But they didn't like working for their father. They would have preferred to been with - a stranger. Because they carry their work home you know. And that's all they get - the topic you see was all about the - the business, how it's getting on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would some families be thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh aye, that's - that was the two words that - respectable citizens they used to call them. And the daredevil - section. It's just the same as - the man doesna take drink, another man - 
does. Variations to living. One man can be happy, the other - where the drink question comes into it it's never a happy family. If it's over - done Oh no, that was - a thing in - when you're thinking what you should drink at that time. And yet they couldn
a buy it. Beer threepence a pint, now it's about - three shillings a pint of beer. So there's no comparison at all. In the new world. You may come back to the life - to see fifty years ago, you wouldna know you're in the same place. Just take 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} now, h
ow it's getting broken up there. There's some people that go away for ten year and come back here, they don't know the place. Even stay here, the only people that you know in the district you've been brought up and even they move out of it, because it's b
een - skyscrapers have been put where there was only - a three storey building.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you remember a distinction of that kind, rough and respe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10438668\charrsid14161784 
ctable, between craftsmen and l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 abourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - you see a labourer was what they call - the lowest - job you 
could get practically. Without he's counted a craftsman. 'Cos he served five years to - see, in the one case, you see, if you're going to be a tradesman you start for about five shillings a week, an an apprentice. But a labourer can get - twenty-one shill
i
ngs - any time for working. But you'll no get - you'll no get the same promise as another fellow. See you start - a tradesman starts with five shillings a week but he ends with - five pound a week. The other fellow, he's in the mire all the time because -
 they could get labourers ten a penny. Buy they canna get the craftsmen you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were labourers families thought of as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well you see they couldna be anything else. Well the families, they had - they couldna afford to - keep them the way th
ey would like to keep them. They could - couldna put a - white collar on for 'em and earn - aye, it was - all the jersey business as I was telling you. Covers up a lot of sins and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh, my mother was a very straight living woman. She didn't like drink, gambling, any of these things. Well these things are kept away you can do wonderful things you know. That was how we were so well fed. You never see whisky in our ho
use, though it was a publicans - it was a small percent that was for illnesses or anything like that was put away. I don't think I ever see my mother taking a drop of whisky in my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you think that your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Very plain woman. She couldna put side on at all. Lovely dressed woman, always tidy. But no - plain clothes all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well you - before 
you got that status you'd got to be well dressed and keep good company. These are - where you get that name is - it's who you - who - who you - run about with. They're usually about the same class as themselves, pick that - you had to pick your - friends 
in these days to get somebody like yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Very often. Of course they were all foot policemen in these days. And - very - all the sins were paltry things. Playing football in
 the street. Standing at the; corners street it was a crime, if you stand at the corner of the street you had - they just come along and said, move on. You had to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What did you think of the policemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - they were pretty ordinary men who were - very - were very poorly paid at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
you frightened of them a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Never had much to do - dealing with them. I played football, that was the only thing I got caught for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well he 
used to be - friendly with the shopkeepers because I think he got a - a little present at the end of the week sort of style, they say they don't and that - that wouldna be allowed nowadays you see but - that's what they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was your home rented?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh the - in these days they called for it. Every - it was - you mostly was all monthly. Monthly paid. And you had a rent book. And the entry was - put in that book and handed back to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What did you feel about your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
You didn't - you didn't know him. You know his - knew where his places were, that was all. His business premises were. But to say that you knew Mr McFee or whoever he was - you - you didna know him. Some of the ti
me you never seen him, it was a clerk, they had clerks that collected the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh aye, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh well, they got used - t
hey get used to it you see and it - it - as I say it was no drinking, the question it can be done. You can bring up a healthy family as we proved in our house. Six of us and hardly a doctor in the house. But the other ones werena so fortunate you know. Go
ing to hospital righ}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784  away wen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
 you get - anything wrong with you. My doctor - when the doctor came to see you in these days you got one and six for his visit. One and six and two bob. And they used to come in a hansome - hansome cab. You know what a hansom
e cab is? The drivers away up in the top. You see them around - well notice in this district, an awful lot of them here, handsome cabs but - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10438668\charrsid14161784 other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784  districts you wouldna se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10438668\charrsid14161784 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
 them at all. Most of the doctors went on foot you see. See, you had so many local d
octors, there was one at every - within a mile or two. Specially in the main streets, they usually took shops in the main - the main streets. Didna go into the side streets or any of these narrow streets you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What difference did it make to your family after your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh made a terrible difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
But you see - he left a good sum of - sum of money you see. And as I tell you - we were only young so - it was all wore out before we were started work really. But helped - put us by for - for a period. But it wouldna have lasted long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you ever get any help from the Guardians or the Parish? Or charity?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I don't think so. If you had money in the bank you see you'd to tell that and you wouldna have 
got it. You'd got to be really like you were - that'd be fraud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you have to move away from above the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well the shop - the shop went with the house. It was sold as - sold at the same time. 'Cos man that had the premises needed the shop t
oo. Needed the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it? Do you remember anyone being made to leave by rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Having a party or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
When a crowd of people gather outside somebody's house and bang saucepans or make a din to show they disapproved of a person, did that ever happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I don't mind seeing that much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you remember an effigy being made ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you given lessons by one of your parents or a tutor, school lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh - well we did, we used to talk about it amongst ourselves and - at night, because you got home lessons in these days. You'd a book and you - you had to copy out handwriting
 and all side of - the specimen was on one side and your writing was on the other. To make you a good wr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
ter. Or to make you a good - a neat writer. In these days - it was a gre}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
t thing to be a good writer you know. Now it's nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents ever give you lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you do afternoon school then or was it all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 All day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Nine o'clock.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What time did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Three o'clock up to seven to - to you get a certain age and then it was four o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 A - a Protestant school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was it a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Corporation school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was it boys or girls or mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Boys and girls mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh it was only - two minutes to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Myself - I went myself. We dived out of doors as we got ready going. Didna wait on your own brother even. He's getting
 ready but he's no finished you just - in a different class maybe, not the same class maybe. See, one's two year older than another and - there's no likely chance of you being in the same class. 'Cos your - if you're moving on - it used to be 1, 2, 3, fou
r, 'til you got up to class six I think it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh, in home for it. There was no - places for it that you could go elsewhere, you had no alternative in these days. But some people had - carried their piece. I
f they'd to go a long way and it was raining, it wasna worth going out you see you could take - have it in the playground or in - a shed - sheds were covered in, you could go and sit away from the rain altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well I was never off it, I was a - had a perfect attendance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 You liked it did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye, I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Never worried me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did they used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 emphasize}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784  certain things as important, manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Tidiness. Wash - you know, keeping yourself clean and washed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh well, the bell run and if - bell rung for three minutes or two minutes. Then the stragglers came in, the late comers rushing - coming in the door. The rest were all seated and you get the odd fellow or odd two - kept coming in five}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 minutes late. And you used to take a note of the absentees every day. Always somebody off you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about ways of speaking, were they keen on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh aye, they were keen on that. Put you right if - you don't - use - used the right words. 'Course they were all - in these days what they called pupil teachers. Young women, maybe only sixteen or seventeen, doing the kiddies at the very bottom and then 
as you get older you get a man - up to the fourth class then it's all - men - men after that. For your English and arithmetic. Getting all these things polished up before you - leave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh well, you see, you got punished in these days, you got the strap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Girls as well as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What sort of things would you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh they strapped - strapped your hands with a - a wee belt or something. Not a be
lt, it's more of a cane sort of thing. So as it wouldna - but I've known fellows to get strapped by the teacher. An old case like that. And that's because he's - frightened the teacher you see. Well the next thing is his folks are sent for. And they go be
fore the headmaster and get the - full report. Good conduct or bad conduct.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What sort of things would you have to do before you got the strap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well, use bad language or anything like that. Get cheeky with one another. The}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 'd grab you for that. Put you at the bottom of the class. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 Bating}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
 it - bring it to see who is - what - going on there. But - there is boys, you know, fight after - school time. And then that's the janitor's job to see that that's taken away right at - attended to right away. Had t
he janitor there watching all the time you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Not a great deal. Because - in these days - you didna make up your mind what you were going to be. They said what you should be but it didna a
lways work out that way. That's not thing I wanted for at all. See I wanted to be a joiner when I started when I was a boy. We got joiner work at school you know. And we got - the use of the tools. Taught by a - what they called a joinery master. Then you
 had the swimming - went to the baths every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents used to ask you what you'd done any school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - well I think they got to know, we lived too near the school, they got to know all about us before - we got time to tell them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did they ever visit the school and meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did the other children at your school come from similar types of home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh much the same. Oh aye, the - the here was a class that never could - be altered, we were all - tidy enough
 but - no - flash - no flashiness at all. You see, the kiddies only got - there were only one in a whole family. That's a different story altogether. They can keep - keep that chap - that boy tidy all the days of his life for very little you know. But whe
n you've five to keep - that's the big - drawback. It's a bigger drawback then than what it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did the teachers single out any children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I don't think so. They - they used to think they did - you k
now, the backward child. There was always a few backwards fellows and - girls too. But - they don't take much - didn't take much notice of them, you just - tried to work them out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh no, not in these
 days. These days in our school everybody went - everyone went home quick enough. Get back - and out again for playing. But it was more simple life you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 There's a lot didna want to participate in them so they - werena suited for it maybe, you couldna tell these things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I - just backwardness a wee bit. If you got two of your brothers beside you you get - maybe more confident. You think you should - do b
etter than they can you know. There's always that - we bit of - I don't know what you call it, jealousy or - competition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you go on to another school after your first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye. I had to go for two - two years. The school I was in gave you
 put to - to a certain standard. Well there's another school - you move away about half a mile to another school for two years. The ones that qualify an examination and the last one is the highest supplementary, that's the top of the school before you lea
ve. If you reach a stage in school that you canna get learned anymore you've got to wait 'til the other fellow - comes up on you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What kind of school was it that you went to, the second school, was that a Corporation school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh yes, but they taug
ht - taught - taught different subjects you see. Special subjects for the last two year. The rest was all ordinary routine. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Reading{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, writing, grammar and that sort of thing. But when you go to these two - if you pass these two you're supposed to be able to go out and get a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How old were you when you first went to this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Twelve. And I come out when I was fourteen. Two -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What time in the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Same times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How long did it take you to get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Ten minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Where did you have your midday meal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh I come home for at again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What did you think of this school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 I think}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
 that's the main thing, if you can get your midday meal it's an awful help all the same. You know, a hot meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What did you think of this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh I thought it was very nice, and - higher class the teachers, men - initials after their name you know, M.A. and that sort of thing. See, they had a - they had - there's no yo
ung people in these schools at all, it's all - getting ready for the - making of age certificate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Was it a boys or mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Mixed. They won't be many - individual schools in these days at all. Corporations were all - boys and girls. I don't
 think they could have - done - run it any other way, it cost a lot of money to do. Not like the Corporation days nowadays who - squander your money, well they've got plenty of money, they're not tight fisted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How did you feel about the teachers at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh I didna like - fancy their job at all. And yet - these men were with it for fifty years. All their lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What were they like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Very plain man. Of course - had bowler hats on in these days and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did they used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4665223\charrsid14161784 emphasize}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784  certain things as important, like manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well you see - if you were smoking in that playground you could get - checked for that. No smoking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about things like manners and tidiness, punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh these are all - all - if somebody 
gets caught for that then he - every day. He come in with his - jacket lying open or anything like that. His lace not tied and the teacher say, get that lace tied. Just the same as it were your ma. But you got used to these things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Well - try to improve your speech. By putting words on the board and pronouncing them the proper way it should be. Everyone - doesnae put it the same way you know. Pronunciation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How would you be punished in this school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 All the things that you get punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh well - we used to - they'd say, go and get to the front of the class. You - anybody that was in that front seat - the rest all knew - get - get watched. The teacher was only five yards away from yo
u, the blackboard - that distance away from you. You're sitting here in the front seat and he's just - five yards - from the blackboard, writing up some things. Explaining them to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What sort of things would they punish you for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Shouting. Speaking during the lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were there any other ways of punishing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh you could - you could be taken into the headmasters room, when you're up in years I'm talking about. But not when you're in these bottom classes, they can do very little ab
out it. But I - I've known - he used the strap very heavily. And their fathers would come down - wanting to know what it was all about. Finish up one man struck the teacher. But he got fined five pound I think that man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you were at the second school did your parents show an interest in your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Well - they knew because - you got - they got a report. What was it - a monthly report or - something like that. How you were getting on. And - inviting your mother or your father with - to come up and see the headmistress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. We never had any - much trouble with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did the other children in this second school come from similar types of home to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh yes. Only you could - you had to go that other sch
ool 'cos they couldna teach you - they were only up to fourth standard you see. And the fifth and sixth is the last two. By that time they were all coming on for fourteen you see. Some handa as long as two years to go, some had about eighteen month. You g
ot away when you were fourteen years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did the teachers at this second school single out children for different treatment from others at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I wouldna say that. The kids - it's the kids mostly, some of the teachers - different natures to some
 - some boys awful spoilt compared to others. Well there's if you went in and said you - anything - teacher - gave you the strap, you know what they would tell you? What were you doing? And of course - if you hadna been doing wrong you wouldna have got th
e
 strap, so don't come in with these stories in here now. Old man used to say that. You - you say, you got the strap yesterday. The oldest son, that was one - he used to be - wasna a cheeky boy but he was - frank sort of boy you know, if the teacher spoke 
to him he got the wind up. Went back and tell his mother about it. But some of them wouldna tell - I never told my folk. I was the same when I went to work, I never carried my troubles home. When I was finished my work that was me finished.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were there any gangs or groups in this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Small skirmishes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, you - if you wanted to play football you put your name in and they picked the - how many they wanted. And the rest all went
 and seen the game. Play another school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 You left that school went you were fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity, or gone on to another school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh I could have went - went in for a bursary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What was that? Like a scholarship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye. But if you did you'd been on to sixteen then. Well I was very fortunate, I starred work the day I left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would you have liked to have gone on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I don't know that I would. I've seen too many fa
ilures at it. It all depends on yourself in this world if you're going to be a success or a failure. But some people cannae think the office work is - as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you left school did you go to any part time education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Not me. I learned more 
at - in me job in a year than I learned in the school for four years. Getting telephone business, telephones to answer. Go messages. Sit down at a desk. Sit down at the bottom desk and work yourself up gradually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No, I don't think so. But if a man has never got the - chance to be in a set job the way I was - and I could have shifted my job a dozen times if I'd have wanted. But it suited me. I'd only a quarter of an hour up to go all that time in that
 fifty years to work. You talking about - that's a secluded life you know. You couldnae pick anything better, nine to - nine - nine to half past five. Who could say having a job like that. I used to think I'd broke a record when I did it. Fifty years - at
 
that. But you see - the job changes as - in cycles, you leave one part and go to the next one. You're always getting something new. But if you didna get that it would be - very monotonous. But of course that's how people have got to serve seven years at a
 trade. The printing trade offer four year with a job and you'd to do seven years. Now they get all for four years for that. Half the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well I wouldnae have liked to have been any other way. S
ee, you get - if you were off your work a day - you'd be fed up. If ever I'd been off a day I'd been glad when it was tomorrow morning. Because it's - it's - get's under your skin. If you were getting days off you wouldnae know what to do. Not only that b
u
t you'd get all the trouble that's knocking about. If you're fully employed for these house all the days of your life, from a schoolboy, so - so it's a case of - environment and - good health. You're need good health for the whole thing you know. Although
 he's a clever fellow when he's at school and pretty awkward when he get to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 While you were at school did you ever have a part time job or any means or earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I could if I - I never took it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Why did you not take it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Well it was the - it was only a Saturday thing and of course Saturday - lazy on the weekend. Aye, we used to play - play for the football club then, I couldna take on anything. We had a match on the Saturday. Oh I was good at mixing into anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh I was in the office right away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I went and applied for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 You saw an advert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye. And - and the funny thing about this - I had three replies. And listen to - wha
t I was supposed to do. When I was - a shipping firm wanted me to serve six months without any pay. And the next one was - sixteen and eightpence a month, four and tuppence a week. And - the one I went to was a pound - five shillings a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What sort of office was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Printing office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well you - you had to attend the phones and - go messages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What hours did you work when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh just about the same time, nine o'clock in the morning to - five - half past five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Any Saturday work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh you worked every Saturday. No Saturdays off in these days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you work all day on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 One o'clock. Nine til one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 You'd - ten days holidays with pay. That was for the staff. But the workers got - no pay when they were off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 And you were paid a pound a month, did you feel that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. But - when you went to these you know, you - you'd - you'd get an advance
 shortly you see. It's an annual advance you - you sign on for. So I managed to get mine up to seven and six the first year. That was how they were showing their value for you you see, you get more valuable to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh she got the whole lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did she give any of it back to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 A shilling, sometimes one and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What would you spend that on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - that's when I started to smoke, I think you got five cigarettes for a penny that time
. Five Woodbines for one penny. That's the cigarettes in the Army when I joined up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh I used to make a few calls buying for them and being - going messages for them and that sort of thi
ng. One man especially was a football referees and he used to let me for his bag on Saturday and his books and - I had five shillings a week and he gave me half a crown. That was a lot of money then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 You - he - o
urs was a limited company you see and you don't see your employers. There are maybe - a hundred and fifty - years old - now. McCorquadales, come from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}, the firm in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
City}}London{\*\xmlclose}, the firm in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Manchester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and the firm in Crewe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 So you had a manager did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh well he was a pretty tough guy, you had to be on your toes all the time. You really - get a report you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you like the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye, I liked it all right. Of course I was a good write
r at the time and that - that was what landed me into it. I think it was my handwriting that - pretty good, copperplate, straight up and down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did the job alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. A lot of people when they're going to an office in thes
e days went to a - a school at night. But I never did that. You see, the - they had - these days schools had the evening schools at that time. And you could go three nights a week and learn certain things as you wanted to learn. Specially for your own tra
d
e you see. There was - it was a college. You could get to that Shefrifs college. The rather successful businessmen. But the night schools, we've still got them yet. That's the - after six o'clock at night, six or seven or something, six or seven thirty. D
uring the winter months only I think it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Is this the office that you stayed in for the whole of the fifty years, can you tell me what the sequence was of your promotion, you started off working as an office boy, then what happened to you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Wel
l you changed from one department to another. You'd to learn whole trades after that you see. Well - I used to go out and look for orders for a while. Then after that I went back inside again to estimate the price a job would cost. If a customer come in f
o
r a - a price, you'd to find out how much it would take to do the job and how long it would - how much material and how long it would take to print. Then you get the answer and he - he show the cost price to the manager, and he fixes his profit onto the -
 
your book and you show what it's - all your details of what the paper so much, setting time so much, printing time so much, if it's a book binding time so much. Paging, numbering your books - all - that's got to be detailed. Then you get the answer and he
 tacks on what he calls his business profit. And then you're - costing. That's costing a job after it's been printed without any estimate. Just to take - taking it at face vale time it took to do the job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Eventually you ended up as a traveler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Partly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 After you'd done these estimates what was the next step up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh you get to a stage that you can go anywhere then you see. You - you don't tie yourself to any. You can go - from one department to another. These - these are all sections, diff
erent sections. But you're supposed to learn one before you go to another one. For to do it right you really need to go to classes. But when you're - doing the actual thing every day you don't - you don't see what good it gets to you. Once you get the - t
he routine in how to start you see and miss nothing out - see the price of paper is terrible you know, now compared to what it used to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How far up the ladder had you got before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - was very - very slowly at that time. I was there for three years and nine months. '16 to 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you came out of the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh it was all changed, the wages we had before we went in was no use. So that - big big increases.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you ever out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What was your final position with the firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh - say - anything at all. I had the full grip of everything by then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you managerial?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. Only one manager in the firm. Then they have what they call senior clerks and junior clerks. They call - tha
t's how they talk to them. And you're a senior clerk when you're about twenty-five supposed to be or twenty - thirty. But you're expected to be able to - take anybody\rquote 
s job - if a man's off. You've got be able to jump in there right away. Otherwise they wo
uldna keep you. Because - that was what keeps you in all these jobs. You're never out of job if - if it's - not doing much in one section the other one may be overflowing with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh I don't k
now - now I would, maybe I done it but not these days. There was no changing - no the same chapping and changing as what - when a man went to a job he had to stick it. Because they werena enough firms to get - make jobs for them. See some trades they can 
t
ell exactly to a few hundred men how much the whole trade uses up. See, the best of a - a printer instead of being on the staff is that a printer gets paid for all his overtime. But a staff man gets - doesna get paid for his overtime at all. But I never d
id any overtime so I don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you were a junior clerk was that like a training period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 That's your training period, that's to see whether you'll make a success.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 How long did that last?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh about five year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 did you belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Never in my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 And professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh they had no trouble with their workers, in the - in the - 1900's, never had any tro
uble at all. There were no strikes in these days at all. It's only since the first world war - gradually - come now to a terrible state. You see the men don' want to strike. You see, if people tell me how did you go through fifty years without ever paying
 a penny for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10438668\charrsid14161784 tradesmen\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
 union. I say, because we werena allowed to, the staff's not allowed to go into a trade union thing in - in my days. You're supposed to belong to the - the firm. A printer can chuck his job the day and start in another printing firm 
tomorrow. Staff man cannae. These jobs are only open once in a - year, every few year you'll get one in the papers but - they all stick to their jobs. If a man's getting a safe wage and he knows what he's going to get - he's got to think of that if he's a
 married man, he canna just chuck up his job and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I don't know about that. No, I think there were - the - the money wasn't so big that they were happier. They wasna always lo
oking for a new job. The way they do nowadays, they hear about somebody that's got a pound a week or two pound more then - they say - right - they preferred security. And that's how so many people was in - these jobs for years and years. They had security
 all the time. And that takes an awful lot for a firm I can stand for fifty years or a hundred years must be some - well managed before it'll ever go that distance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Some people say that in those days there was a division between trained craftsmen and o
ther workers, did you feel that was so in your profession?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Oh well, they shouldn't - there wasn't in our time because they knew that - they knew the conditions that the one man has to serve seven years as I was telling you. The other fellows hasn't t
o serve anything. He gets a good wage from the very day he starts. The other fellow has to work for six shillings a week or five shillings a week. That - all balances up one way to the other. He's spending that seven years so he'll get a good pay - this p
r
oves that the printers are one of the best paid trades - and sheltered trades. No - rain or anything like that. They're - under cover for fifty years. From a drop of water falling on top of their head. And if that's not security - I don't know what you wa
n
t. But if a man's discontented he'll change just the same. But you - these are only odd cases, I've known fellows got big headed, fellows that I taught the game, estimate and that. They went away and thought they could go in another firm and just step in 
r
ight away. You know see a job in six month. And then he try to get back and he couldna get in again. You see when you've got a job like that - if you're - you'll no do it if you're a married man, a married man thinks twice before he does it. A single fell
ow can chuck his job and take a chance. He's the only one that's going to suffer. But - in these days - very few jobs were secure. You could be a great tradesman and be walking about the streets doing nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh no, in a full time job. Because if you had a part time job you were trying to do something clever and - you would - you - you'l
\rquote d lose the benefit if you - altogether. It's like a part time football player
. Well - he only gets about half his pay for being a part time man. And - he's got to - make provisions for other three days that he's no doing anything. Knocking about spare. But the other fellow, he's - getting his full weeks pay, he knows what he's doi
ng.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you general attitude to life change after you started work do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
No, I was - all I was - my aim was getting work keeping working and - keeping really not too heartbreaking. 'Cos I picked my job. These people are talking about fort
y hours a week. I - I never worked any longer and I'm fifty years in the job. And I only worked forty hours a week all the days of my life. But then - the advantage again with a printer again, he goes in at eight in the morning. You come in at nine o'cloc
k
, sitting on your bottom. No machines to start or anything like that. That man must go in there at eight o'clock and that machine must be running at a minute past eight. And that machine, they can tell how many runs that machine'll do They can print a who
le book in one sheet. A book of sixty-four pages can be done - in one - turn of the machine. And then it's all folded and - cut down to a book shape. Folded in book shape.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you continue to live at home after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Never away from home all the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10438668\charrsid14161784 days of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784  my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What about with your brothers and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 My mother's attitude towards me was - you mind outside and I'll mind inside. And that was her idea. But \endash 
 any bad news, we never gave her anything like that at all. These were all - allowed to fly by. The other brothers comes in and say, oh I had a rotten job today. Murderous job or something like that. I wouldna think of saying that.
 'Course my mother said I'd live 'til I was a hundred you know, when I was sixteen she said that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your relationship with your brothers and your sister change at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 I was the only one that was in a staff job you see. The other ones had - ha
d to start early in the morning. Engineers. One was an engineer. One was n the shipyards. And the other was a - waiter, and he had a good job always, he was a deck steward in liners. Tucking in the ladies wi' - afternoon tea. Away for six weeks - }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10438668\charrsid14161784 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Mediterranean}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 {\*\xmlclose}
. Walking about in his white cap and his white sash. Botts had to be polished, his collar had to be white.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 When you started work did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh I was a right busy man on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
I went to the - like - Sunday evening. I always had a great sleep on a Sunday. I got my breakfast in bed on a Sunday. Eventually she said, to my sister and that, oh, she said, you'll as well gi' him his breakfast in bed, you get peace like that you know
, he's not - then he'll - the next thing he'll ask for is the papers, Sunday paper. Then the next thing you hear is, you'd better get up and get cleaned, there's folk coming here, or something like that, you know, to get you out. Get up. Go start looking 
for the bath, shaving and all that you know. That's the only time you hear a family together these days. In the day, they've all got different jobs and different times. Wheareas a Sunday they're all together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you have to go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh nae Sunday school after - no, no, up to I was fourteen. Stopped it after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Used to go to the meetings and listen to them, that was about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Which meetings would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
These local ones here. They used - got to maybe - Cathcart, South Side, all in different places. Municipal. You know, they werena that big - elections. You know the M.P. The Prime Minister came from Hutchestontwon at one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 What were your views at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh well - I was a Labourman at that time. See, if you were not in a Labourite job you change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Why did you think that, why were you a Labour man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Well I thought the trades union is a great thing up to a point but - it wou
ldn't - when it gets - dogmatic and tries to rule things and don't want any - thing said against them you know, just the same as I said years ago, the trades union movement - has - cost this country a fortune. Because - they make demands and they cause un
e
mployment and they had nothing of that when there were no trade unions. Well this union here had a petition, but that was for unemployment. Some firms - firms we knew - Printers Trade Union got a week - weekly allocation you know. That's no the same thing
 
as this at all. I said it was all right to - to - too powerful, and it might lead to anarchy in this country. They might want to take a fellow over you see. The next thing you'll see in this country is maybe there'll be no Prime Minister, that's what - we
're edging towards that in a few years. I hope it doesna come to that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you vote in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 1919. Oh aye, I voted - I voted Labour then. 1918, 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you ever feel under any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, I wasna interested close enough to it as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Were you ever a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you ever work for a party at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Apart from going to these meetings did you ever take part in any other political activity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
You told me earlier something of how you spent your spare time when you were at school, did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way or did you do different things when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No, just much the same thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you go out in the evenings at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 
Aye, went out and had a crack with the boys at the corner, that was all. As I'm telling you, each corner had about six standing at it. No such a thing nowadays. -And the bobby 
used to come along and say, move on, that was all. You moved to the next corner. When he went away we go back to the corner you'd left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 You'd jut go and have a chat would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh aye, talk about - football and - all the sports. Mostly sports it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you make any new friends, boys or girls, at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 No. There was no girls at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did you have any special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Oh well, we used to keep to the same - friends all - always.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 The ones you were at school with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2908818 RF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Aye. That's if they were still in the district you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4420895 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12524115\charrsid14161784 Did your parents meet your friends?
